#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.41:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.41:0.2"
msgid "5. Rohitassavagga "
msgstr "5. With Rohitassa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Samādhibhāvanāsutta "
msgstr "41. Ways of Developing Immersion Further "

# NOTE: Bhavana has the normal sense of “makeing more of something”. Samadhibhavana is not how to get samadhi, but how to enhance and grow it. The English term development is ambiguous here so I clarify.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.41:1.1"
msgid "“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of developing immersion further. "

msgctxt "an4.41:1.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.41:1.3"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "There is a way of developing immersion further that leads to blissful meditation in the present life. "

msgctxt "an4.41:1.4"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ñāṇadassanappaṭilābhāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "There is a way of developing immersion further that leads to gaining knowledge and vision. "

msgctxt "an4.41:1.5"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satisampajaññāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "There is a way of developing immersion further that leads to mindfulness and awareness. "

msgctxt "an4.41:1.6"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "There is a way of developing immersion further that leads to the ending of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.45, sc2
msgctxt "an4.41:2.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārāya saṃvattati? "
msgstr "And what is the way of developing immersion further that leads to blissful meditation in the present life? "

msgctxt "an4.41:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "an4.41:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the way of developing immersion further that leads to blissful meditation in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.41:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ñāṇadassanappaṭilābhāya saṃvattati? "
msgstr "And what is the way of developing immersion further that leads to gaining knowledge and vision? "

msgctxt "an4.41:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ālokasaññaṃ manasi karoti, divāsaññaṃ adhiṭṭhāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant focuses on the perception of light, concentrating on the perception of day, "

msgctxt "an4.41:3.3"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "regardless of whether it’s night or day. "

msgctxt "an4.41:3.4"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, they develop a mind that’s full of radiance. "

msgctxt "an4.41:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ñāṇadassanappaṭilābhāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the way of developing immersion further that leads to gaining knowledge and vision. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.41:4.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satisampajaññāya saṃvattati? "
msgstr "And what is the way of developing immersion further that leads to mindfulness and awareness? "

msgctxt "an4.41:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno viditā vedanā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant knows feelings as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "an4.41:4.3"
msgid "viditā saññā … pe … viditā vitakkā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti. "
msgstr "They know perceptions as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. They know thoughts as they arise, as they remain, and as they go away. "

msgctxt "an4.41:4.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satisampajaññāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the way of developing immersion further that leads to mindfulness and awareness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.41:5.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati? "
msgstr "And what is the way of developing immersion further that leads to the ending of defilements? "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī viharati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates. "

#. VAR: atthaṅgamo → atthagamo (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.41:5.3"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form. "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.4"
msgid "iti vedanā, iti vedanāya samudayo, iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of feeling. "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.5"
msgid "iti saññā, iti saññāya samudayo, iti saññāya atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of perception. "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.6"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā, iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo, iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of choices. "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.7"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti. "
msgstr "Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’ "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, samādhibhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the way of developing immersion further that leads to the ending of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.41:5.9"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso samādhibhāvanā. "
msgstr "These are the four ways of developing immersion further. "

msgctxt "an4.41:5.10"
msgid "Idañca pana metaṃ, bhikkhave, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ pārāyane puṇṇakapañhe: "
msgstr "And it was in this connection that I said in ‘The Way to the Beyond’, in ‘The Questions of Puṇṇaka’: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.46, sc6
msgctxt "an4.41:6.1"
msgid "‘Saṅkhāya lokasmiṃ paroparāni, "
msgstr "‘Having surveyed the world high and low, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.41:6.2"
msgid "Yassiñjitaṃ natthi kuhiñci loke; "
msgstr "they’re not shaken by anything in the world. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.41:6.3"
msgid "Santo vidhūmo anīgho nirāso, "
msgstr "Peaceful, unclouded, untroubled, with no need for hope, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.41:6.4"
msgid "Atāri so jātijaranti brūmī’”ti. "
msgstr "they’ve crossed over birth and old age, I declare.’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.41:6.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
